THE NINES OBSERVATION:
  epsilon = 0.0015979823200311139265
  1/625   = 0.0016 = 0.001599999... (repeating)
  Difference: epsilon - 1/625 = -2.01767996889e-6
  epsilon / (1/625)           = 0.998738950019

  Repunit identity: 0.0016 = 0.001599999... (base-10 repeating expansion)
  625 = 5^4 = 625. 1/625 terminates in decimal (factors 2^4 * 5^4 = 10^4).
  The error epsilon ~ 1/625.789 is close to 1/625 to within 0.13%.

CONTEXT: WHY beta_0 = 299 + pi/10?
